{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"e07988a3-94dc-4554-9acc-6229c68ef9b0","content":"Use MAUI's conditional compilation with `#if` directives in `MauiProgram.cs`:\n\n```csharp\npublic static MauiApp CreateMauiApp()\n{\n    var builder = MauiApp.CreateBuilder();\n    builder.UseMauiApp<App>();\n\n#if ANDROID\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Android.AndroidNotificationService>();\n#elif IOS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.iOS.IosNotificationService>();\n#elif WINDOWS\n    builder.Services.AddSingleton<INotificationService, Platforms.Windows.WindowsNotificationService>();\n#endif\n\n    return builder.Build();\n}\n```\n\nEach implementation lives under its respective `Platforms/` folder (e.g., `Platforms/Android/AndroidNotificationService.cs`), which is already conditionally compiled per-platform by the default `.csproj` globs. This guarantees only the correct implementation is compiled and registered on each target, so it won't break on any platform.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"8118367e-d981-4000-a1e6-ee8b1b731588","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about .NET MAUI dependency injection — specifically how to register platform-specific implementations of an `INotificationService` in `MauiProgram.cs`. This is a general knowledge question, not a codebase-specific task.","outputTokens":328,"requestId":"D44B:29787D:1D4F6E8:20F8699:6A07C409"},"id":"f5896805-9e19-4468-8a4b-a92d98ecaca0","timestamp":"2026-05-16T01:10:40.720Z","parentId":"954763bd-2653-47b4-88cc-d888ae0cae13"}
